author: Jason Brennan
title: TV | Live Rugby World Cup 2015
text:
The details for today's matches are below:
4.30pm: Pool D: Canada v Romania
Kick-Off: 4.45pm
Stadium: Leicester City Stadium
This is not a glamour tie by any stretch of the imagination, but as this World Cup has proven, the so-called weaker sides are capable of upping their game and producing some top class rugby. Canada have produced some good performances so far as the plucky underdogs, and hope to finally pick up a win having tested, but ultimately failing against France over the weekend.
7.30pm: Pool A: Fiji v Uruguay
Kick-Off: 8.00pm
Stadium: Stadium MK
The pool's two most unfancied sides of Pool A battle it out in the day's late kick-off. The nations have only met on two previous occasions, with Fiji taking the honours both times, and each team is expected to enter this match playing for what is likely to be a fourth place position. Expect to see the ball thrown around a lot, as both sides have so far shown they're here to play attacking football.
